{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a40874e9-a877-45e0-807d-38fb50932cf4","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 drops support for older frameworks.** Specifically:\n\n- **`net462`** — MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework **4.7.2** (`net472`).\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — MSTest v3 requires at minimum **.NET 6.0** (`net6.0`). .NET Core 3.1 is no longer supported.\n- **`net5.0`** — Also unsupported; .NET 5 is out of support and MSTest v3 targets `net6.0`+.\n\n### To migrate, you'd need to update `TargetFrameworks` to something like:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net472</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\n(or `net8.0` if you can target a current LTS release)\n\n### Summary\n\n| Current TFM       | MSTest v3 Compatible? | Minimum Replacement |\n|--------------------|----------------------|---------------------|\n| `net462`           | ❌                    | `net472`            |\n| `netcoreapp3.1`   | ❌                    | `net6.0`            |\n| `net5.0`           | ❌                    | `net6.0`            |\n\nAll three of your current targets would need updating before MSTest v3 will work. Would you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"160fbf11-bcbb-430b-a69e-9d45bb332980","outputTokens":355,"requestId":"240A:341029:4B500F:506649:6A03112F"},"id":"4276849b-cb6f-4137-80f4-cb2baf8d9ae7","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:38:36.463Z","parentId":"e2651ecf-7051-4716-8c03-562bb51b9e0a"}
